&lt;h3&gt;OUR VISION&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When people use our technology to &quot;bridge the gap&quot; between the physical and digital worlds, they don’t just capture reality - they create a new one. In this new reality, they are smarter, more productive, more streamlined, and more creative - because they have the digital foundation to build the world they want to live in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That’s what NavVis offers in all our products and services: the tools to not just map the world as it is, but to pave the way to a better future. To forge something new. Physical or digital, there is only one reality. And it’s the reality NavVis empowers people to build better.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;THE OPPORTUNITY&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;5918&quot; data-local-id=&quot;ab633f54ba63&quot;&gt;As part of our Enterprise Professional Services organization, you&#39;ll join a customer project team that delivers a comprehensive digital twin of our customers’ globally distributed factory network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;5918&quot; data-local-id=&quot;ab633f54ba63&quot;&gt;For a leading global Oil &amp;amp; Gas company, we are 3D scanning refineries across the US, Europe, and Asia, covering a footprint of more than 80 million square meters, one of the largest reality capture projects in the industry. As a 3D data admin, you will manage, control, and deliver 3D data for the end customer&#39;s facilities as part of a team that owns quality assurance and data delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;5918&quot; data-local-id=&quot;ab633f54ba63&quot;&gt;You will gain hands-on insight into executing a large-scale customer project, working closely with our project managers and 3D scanning partners, and play a key role in its success. This role suits someone with strong interest in spatial technology and 3D data management who takes ownership in a customer-centric, fast-paced global environment.&lt;/p&gt;
